# Deploying {{ name }}

**STOP: No local server. Do NOT run `manage.py runserver`.**
**Deploy = SSH + Docker build on Carlos via `.ymir/deploy.py`.**

## Deploy to dev (takes 2-3 min — run detached)

```bash
cd /workspace/{{ name }} && nohup python3 .ymir/deploy.py dev > /tmp/deploy.log 2>&1 & disown
sleep 30 && cat /tmp/deploy.log   # repeat until ✓ health check passed or ✗
```

Dev app is at `http://100.68.2.106:<port>/` — served at root, **no slug prefix**.

## Diagnosing errors

**Always use logs — never synthetic test data:**

```bash
python3 .ymir/deploy.py logs dev        # tail 50 lines of container output
python3 .ymir/deploy.py logs dev 200    # tail 200 lines
```

Read the actual traceback. Fix the specific error. Re-test with the real failing scenario.

## Commands

```bash
python3 .ymir/deploy.py status                # state + flag values
python3 .ymir/deploy.py verify [dev|prod]     # HTTP health check
python3 .ymir/deploy.py logs [dev|prod] [N]   # tail container logs (default: dev, 50 lines)
python3 .ymir/deploy.py flag-add <flag> [desc]
python3 .ymir/deploy.py flag-delete <flag>
python3 .ymir/deploy.py activate <flag>       # flag ON in dev
python3 .ymir/deploy.py deactivate <flag>     # flag OFF in dev
python3 .ymir/deploy.py prod                  # dark-launch (flags OFF)
python3 .ymir/deploy.py release <flag>        # flag ON in prod
python3 .ymir/deploy.py rollback <flag>       # flag OFF in prod
```

## Rules

- No `docker` commands directly. No `python3 ymir.py`. No `sudo`. No `Dockerfile` edits.
- Always deploy dev → verify → then prod.
- New features must be behind a feature flag (`feature_flags.yaml`).
- Claim done only after verifying with the **real failing input**, not a synthetic file.
